parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front axle can cause the vehicle to shake or vibrate, leading to loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
The failure of the rear axle can cause the wheel to come loose or fly off, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a loud noise or vibration from the rear axle
the wheel comes loose or flies off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to slip or hesitate, leading to loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle experiences a loud thumping sound
the transmission delays when shifting into reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure - Steering Column Wiring
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column wiring can cause a fire, leading to a potential loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Smoke or burning smell from under the hood
wires in the steering column on fire

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbag light to stay on and potentially lead to a fire, which can cause injuries and accidents.
The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a potential loss of vehicle control and accidents.
Intermittent stalling can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents and injuries.
The failure of the trailing arm assembly can cause the vehicle to make loud noises when making turns, potentially leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Loud popping or cracking noise when making right turns
